  "texts": [
    "Figure 2 stresses the difference between the two groups visually by the use of box plots.",
    "The center of gravity for the prox group is not only lower but also less broad, compared to the plaus group, meaning that even though the variance stretches over the entire x-axis, the gross of the relative feature spans for this group lies between 22% and 42% (20% and 39%) for the RF (ANN) classifier.",
    "In contrast, the relative feature span for the plaus group lies mainly between 39% and 86% (40% and 86%) for the RF (ANN) classifier.",
    "To add more detail, we split up the plaus group into exogenous and endogenous counterfactual algorithms.",
    "Endogenous counterfactual algorithms provide explanations based on observed instances, while exogenous counterfactual algorithms give explanations based on unobserved instances (Crupi et al. 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Endogenous counterfactual algorithms provide explanations based on observed instances, while exogenous counterfactual algorithms give explanations based on unobserved instances (Crupi et al. 2022)."
